===Noun===
[[Image:Smiley_head_happy.png|80px|thumb|A "smiley"]]
{{en-noun}}

# {{context|typography}} A simplified representation of a smiling face using keyboard characters; usually either <tt>[[&nbsp;:)|:)]]</tt> or <tt>[[&nbsp;:-)|:-)]]</tt> (with the [[colon]] representing eyes, the optional [[hyphen]] representing a nose, and the [[parenthesis]] representing a mouth). Some messaging software automatically replaces these with [[smiley face]] images.
# {{context|Internet}} A smiley face image that has replaced a character-sequence smiley.
# {{context|typography|Internet}} ''More generally'', a sequence of characters representing a different facial expression, or a corresponding image that has replaced it.
# {{slang}} Having one's throat slit from side to side.

